  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Wondrous item, (requires attunement by a cleric, druid, or paladin)</em></p><p>This necklace has 1d4 + 2 magic beads made from aquamarine, black pearl, or topaz. It also has many nonmagical beads made from stones such as amber, bloodstone, citrine, coral, jade, pearl, or quartz. If a magic bead is removed from the necklace, that bead loses its magic.</p><p>Six types of magic beads exist. The GM decides the type of each bead on the necklace or determines it randomly. A necklace can have more than one bead of the same type. To use one, you must be wearing the necklace. Each bead contains a spell that you can cast from it as a bonus action (using your spell save DC if a save is necessary). Once a magic bead's spell is cast, that bead can't be used again until the next dawn.</p><p>Use the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.tables.RollTable.XHTUTUXdyzcPbodw]{Necklace of Prayer Beads} table and refer to the table below for detailed descriptions on each bead</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>d20</strong></th><th><strong>Bead ofâ€¦</strong></th><th><strong>Spell</strong></th><th><strong>Guide Price per Bead (gp)</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1-6</td><td>Blessing</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.8dzaICjGy6mTUaUr]{Bless}</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td>7-12</td><td>Curing</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.uUWb1wZgtMou0TVP]{Cure Wounds} (2nd level) or @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.F0GsG0SJzsIOacwV]{Lesser Restoration}</td><td>4,000</td></tr><tr><td>13-16</td><td>Favor</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.WzvJ7G3cqvIubsLk]{Greater Restoration}</td><td>32,000</td></tr><tr><td>17-18</td><td>Smiting</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.7UwUjJ6owIQkEPrs]{Branding Smite}</td><td>1,500</td></tr><tr><td>19</td><td>Summons</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.fkREcytuZ8sngWtC]{Planar Ally}</td><td>128,000</td></tr><tr><td>20</td><td>Wind Walking</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.8PJAsHmbu6UgDHC0]{Wind Walk}</td><td>96,000</td></tr></tbody></table><section class=\"secret foundry-note\" id=\"secret-7DOXr3q6fDOOCepZ\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Each activity uses correspond to the number of beads of that type available, and should be adjusted to match the proper values. The item's uses as a whole track the number of Beads of Curing.</p><p>Additionally, the guide price is a guide only and should be adjusted accordingly to reflect the Dungeon Master's world.</p></section>",
